- content_for :foot do
  :css
    .row {
      margin-bottom: 4em;
    }

    h2 { font-family: Dosis; }
    h3 { font-family: Dosis; }

    .row h3 {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
    .row h3 {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }

    h2 + p {
      margin-top: 1em;
    }
    h3 + p {
      margin-top: 1em;
    }

    .jumbotron {
      height: 25em;
      padding-bottom: 4em;
      margin-bottom: 6em;
      background-image: url('http://lorempixel.com/1140/486/food/2');
    }

    .book {
      background-color: #eee;
      height: 18em;
      padding: 1em 2em;
      margin-top: 6em;
    }

    .bar-section {
      background-color: #666;
      color: #efefef;
      padding-top: 2em;
      padding-bottom: 2em;
    }

.row
  .col-md-12.text-center(style="margin-top: 2em")
    %h1(style="font-weight: bold")
      Want to make your imagination real?
      %p
        %small
          Learn to design 3D printable models, programming, and the art of subversion.


.jumbotron
  .row
    .col-md-offset-6.col-md-6
      .book
        %h2(style="font-family: Helvetica; margin-bottom: 2em")
          Designing with OpenSCAD
          %br
          %small A young lady's first enchiridion

        %p
          %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-primary(href="https://leanpub.com/designing_with_openscad")
            Buy eBook from $9.99


.row
  .col-md-offset-2.col-md-8
    %h2
      Make your ideas real.
    %hr/
    %p.lead
      Nowadays, it's easier than ever to make your ideas real. All you need
      is to design a 3D model to feed into a 3D printer. But if mainstream CAD 
      software seems hard to learn and too expensive, then it's time to read
      %i Designing with OpenSCAD.

.row
  .col-md-12
    %hr/
  .col-md-offset-2.col-md-8.text-center
    %h2
      What is OpenSCAD?
    %p.lead
      OpenSCAD is a free and simple programming language 
      used to make parametric 3D models for 3D printing.
  .col-md-offset-2.col-md-4
    %h3.text-center
      Combine 3D shapes.
    %pre(style="height: 250px; margin-bottom: 2em")
      :preserve
        difference() {
          cube([10, 10, 10]);
          cylinder(10, 5, 5);
        }
  .col-md-4
    %h3.text-center
      To make 3D models.
    %img(src="http://lorempixel.com/360/250")
  .col-md-12
    %hr/



.row
  .col-md-offset-2.col-md-8
    %h2
      Programming is literacy.
    %hr/
    %p.lead
      Software is eating the world. Every industry is changing as software changes the
      way we live, work, and play.  OpenSCAD is a good start for learning how to 
      program, as a stepping stone to participating in the future. 


.row.bar-section.text-center
  .col-md-4
    %h3
      Best Practices
    %p
      Learn how to design 3D printable objects
  .col-md-4
    %h3
      Much Pictures
    %p
      Learn how to 3D print things
  .col-md-4
    %h3
      Naughtiness
    %p
      Learn how to program objects


.row
  .col-md-offset-2.col-md-8
    %h2
      The art of subversion.
    %hr/
    %p.lead
      New technologies allow us to do things we weren't able to do before, easier,
      cheaper, and faster. Inevitably, they allow us the possibility of changing
      established social order and power structure. What are the things we can do with 3D
      printing that people don't want us to do?


